  "doc_id": "17903",
  "text": "LG and KS meltwater rivers were monitored for discharge, suspended sediment concentrations, and electrical conductivity (EC) at stable bedrock sections ( Figure 1 ) using methods previously described by [CITATION_1] (Text S1 in the supporting information). pH was recorded manually when samples were taken using a handheld Hanna® HI9124 meter with standard glass electrode probe at LG and continuously using an ISFET (ion-selective field-effect transistor) Honeywell Durafet® pH sensor at KS. Handheld meters were calibrated daily using National Institute of Standards and Technology-certified pH 7 and 10 buffers (Fisherbrand   TM   ) , and the ISFET sensor was calibrated monthly with low ionic strength pH 4.01 and pH 6.96 buffers (Reagecon). Errors are estimated at ±0.05 pH units.",
